The paper discusses training agents using Deep Reinforcement Learning in mobile robotics, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the architecture and network design of the agents, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of 3D environments and simulations suggests a possible connection to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of limited hardware resources, which is a common topic in Neural Networks (cs.NE).
